E-Lite offers the most comprehensive voice controlled smart home experience with Alexa. Control your lighting and other devices hands free. Just say it, E-Lite will obey. 

Here’s a step by step guide:
(1). Login with E-Lite Account.
(2). Turn on Light devices and connect network;
(3). IMPORTANT: You can rename the devices On Site. So if you rename a device “Livingroom Light”, then Echo will get that same name after discovered the devices in Step 7;
(4). Download Amazon "Alexa" app from Amazon Market, Google Play or iOS App Store, and connect Echo with "Alexa" app;
(5). Search the Alexa Skills directory for "E-Lite";
(6). Click Enable skill of "E-Lite", then input your account username, password on the linking page;
(7). Talk to Echo "“Alexa,discover devices.”. Wait till Echo says "Discover is completed";
(8). Now all setup is done. Try talk to Echo to control your devices.

Here are the voice commands E-Lite has:

Lights:
* Alexa, turn on livingroom light
* Alexa, turn off livingroom light
* Alexa, set the livingroom light to 20 percent
